<p class="csshide">&nbsp;</p>		<div class="item"  id="newsblock27286">		
			<div class="newstitle1">
				<span id="star_27286">
									</span>
				<a href="/story/27286/Software_patents_cause_of_rise_in_patent_suits_says_US_gov">Software patents cause of rise in patent suits, says US gov</a>
			</div>
			
			<div class="newssubheader1">
			Linked by <a href="/editor/11">Thom Holwerda</a>			on Fri 23rd Aug 2013 08:54 UTC			</div>
			
			<div class="newscontent1">
				<a href="/topics/44"><img src="http://www.osnews.com/images/icons/44.gif" alt="Legal" class="timg" align="left" title="Legal" /></a>
			Ars Technica looks at a government report on the rise in patent lawsuits, and concludes that <a href="http://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2013/08/new-govt-report-on-patent-lawsuits-is-tepid-but-shows-a-clear-trend/">most of it is caused by software patents</a>.
</p>
<div class="cquote"><p>As is clearly visible in the graph above, the data shows that many more companies are getting sued than were a few years ago. That's true even though the number of lawsuits has held relatively steady over the last 5 years. The increase in defendants, the next graph shows, is driven by software patents.</p></div>
<p>
It's right there in the data. The problem is, of course, that software patents are the bread and butter of Microsoft's and Apple's campaign against their competitors, and as such, there is zero chance of the US government stepping in to finally ban these ridiculous patents. As long as the two largest technology companies rely on software patents, nothing will be done about them.</p></div>
			<div class="newsfooter1">
			
			<a href="/share/27286/Software_patents_cause_of_rise_in_patent_suits_says_US_gov" title="Email this article"><img src="/images/email2.gif" alt="E-mail" title="Email this article" /></a>
			<a href="/print/27286/Software_patents_cause_of_rise_in_patent_suits_says_US_gov" title="Print this article"><img src="/images/printer2.gif" alt="Print" title="Print this article" /></a>
