			<div class="newscontent1">
				<a href="/topics/34"><img src="http://www.osnews.com/images/icons/34.gif" alt="Internet &amp;amp; Networking" class="timg" align="left" title="Internet &amp;amp; Networking" /></a>
			<div class="cquote"><p>Worldwide internet traffic <a href="http://news.sky.com/story/1129847/google-outage-internet-traffic-plunges-40-percent">plunged by around 40%</a> as Google services suffered a complete black-out, according to web analytics experts.
</p><p>
The tech company said all of its services from Google Search to Gmail to YouTube to Google Drive went down for between one and five minutes last night.
</p><p>
The reason for the outage is not yet known, and Google refused to provide any further information when contacted by Sky News Online.
</p><p>
According to web analytics firm GoSquared, global internet traffic fell by around 40% during the black-out, reflecting Google's massive grip on the web.</p></div>
<p>
Woah.</p></div>
